  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nursing care for traumatized children in Bethlehem</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children of Peace funds schooling and therapy for 30 children, age 5-17, in the Bethlehem area of Palestine. These children have been physically, mentally or emotionally traumatized by the conflict in the region and can not find adequate care in the standard school system. Care will include regular medical screenings, vision, dental and hearing testing, nutritional assessments, in-home visits and emergency response needs. The nursing care provider has been identified but funds are needed.</narrative>
  </description>
